(firstQuint)Temperature Measurement in Post-Anesthesia Care Units.

 Several measurements of temperature will be taken at 30 minute intervals during surgery under general anesthesia and in the post operative care unit.

 Measurements will be taken as follows: - esophagus using an internal stethoscope - urinary bladder using a catheter - ear canal - skin of the forehead using adhesive devices(4 thermometers) - axilla ("armpit") using adhesive devices(2 thermometers) - mouth - skin of the upper chest.

